      {
        "name": "Chandra Yogas",
        "description": "Your kundli has 4 chandra yogas.",
        "yoga_list": [
          {
            "has_yoga": true,
            "name": "Sunafa Yoga",
            "description": "If any planet other than the sun occupies the second house from moon sign then such a birth chart has the Sunafa yoga. This yoga is known to bring, good fortune and wealth. Generally such individuals are quite natured and they enjoy activities like music and poetry. In this chart Venus is in the 2nd house from Moon."
          },
          {
            "has_yoga": true,
            "name": "Anafa Yoga",
            "description": "Anafa Yoga is as a result of a benefic planet (except Sun, Rahu and Ketu) in the twelfth house from Moon. The native of Anafa yoga enjoys good health. They will be able to get people on their side with their charm and wit. They will be a master in communication and  may also be interest in humanitarian causes and charitable acts. In this chart planet Mars is in the 12th house from Moon."
          },
          {
            "has_yoga": true,
            "name": "Durudhara Yoga",
            "description": "Durudhara Yoga is formed as a result of planets (except Sun, Rahu and Ketu) being on either side of Moon. Those with Durudhara Yoga are blessed with many luxuries in life. They are known to enjoy theses  comforts of life, but they will be generous and charitable too. In this chart planets Venus and Mars are on either side of Moon."
          },
          {
            "has_yoga": true,
            "name": "Kemadruma Yoga",
            "description": "Kemadruma Yoga is formed when the second and twelfth house from the moon is not occupied by any planet (except Sun, Rahu and Ketu). This leaves either side of Moon empty, making it weak.  Struggles and Poverty is typical of a person born with Kemadruma Yoga.  Being away from family and loved ones is also seen in such natives. Some remedies that are advised to minimise the negative effects of Kemadruma yoga is: Fasting on Purnima days for four consecutive years is known to minimise the negative effects of Kemadruma yoga. You may begin this fast starting from a Purnima that happens on a Monday or even from the day of Chitra nakshatra whenever it falls on a Monday. Pay a visit  to Siva's temple on Mondays and perform abhisheka using cow\u2019s milk on Shivalinga Worshipping Lord Shiva and goddess Parvati is advised. Reciting the Shivapanchakshari mantra \u2018Om Namah Shivaya\u2019 with a Rudraksha mala is also specially helpful. Reading the Sri Sukta regularly and keeping a Dakshinavarti shell in the house is also helpful. Fill water in the  Dakshinavarti shell and puse this water to perform abhisheka on the idol of of Goddess Lakshmi. Wearing a Sri Yantra set in silver with a pearl is also especially helpful for Kemadruma natives."
          }
